al: ~$2,497 USD\n- Remaining for Flights: ~$503 USD (INSUFFICIENT)\n\n**REQUIRED CLARIFICATION:**\nThe original task states \"My budget is 3k\" but doesn't specify if this includes international flights. We need to know:\n\n1. **Is the $3,000 budget absolute?** If yes, we must reduce European costs significantly\n2. **Can the budget be increased for flights?** If yes, what's the new total?\n3. **Should the itinerary be shortened?** (e.g., 10 days instead of 14)\n4. **Are there alternative travel options?** (e.g., budget airlines instead of trains)\n\n**IMPACT ON ITINERARY:**\nIf $3,000 is absolute and must include flights, I recommend:\n- Reduce trip to 10 days (save 4 hotel nights = ~€520)\n- Remove 2-3 cities (save hotels + trains)\n- Use budget airlines for some European legs instead of trains\n- This would free up ~$800-1,000 for international flights\n\nPlease clarify the budget constraint so I can adjust the itinerary accordingly.", "recipient_id": 0}]}
